an, K., Simonelli, P., Nejstgaard, J.C., Putzeys, S., Microzooplankton grazing and phytoplankton growth in marine mesocosms with increased CO2 levels (2008) Biosciences, 5, pp. 1145-1156; Suffrian, K., Schulz, K.G., Gutowska, M.A., Riebesell, U., Cellular pH measurements in Emiliania huxleyi reveal pronounced membrane proton permeability (2011) New Phytol, 190, pp. 595-608; Tada, K., Pithakpol, S., Yano, R., Montani, S., Carbon and nitrogen content of Noctiluca scintillans in the Seto Inland Sea, Japan (2000) J Plankton Res, 22, pp. 1203-1211; Thomsen, H.A., (1992) Plankton I de Indre Danske Farvande, , Havforskning fra Miljøstyrelsen nr. 11/1992. Miljøstyrelsen, Copenhagen (in Danish with English abstract); Tortell, P.D., DiTullio, G.R., Sigman, D.M., Morel, F.M.M., CO2 effects on taxonomic composition and nutrient utilization in an Equatorial Pacific phytoplankton assemblage (2002) Mar Ecol Prog Ser, 236, pp. 37-43; Trimborn, S., Lundholm, N., Thoms, S., Richter, K.U., Inorganic carbon acquisition in potentially toxic and non-toxic diatoms: The effect of pH-induced changes in seawater carbonate chemistry (2008) Physiol Plant, 133, pp. 92-105; Umani, S.F., Beran, A., Parlato, S., Virgilio, D., Noctiluca scintillans MACARTNEY in the Northern Adriatic Sea: Long-term dynamics, relationships with temperature and eutrophication, and role in the food web (2004) J Plankton Res, 26, pp. 545-561; Wright, S.W., Van Den Enden, R.L., Pearce, I., Davidson, A.T., Phytoplankton community structure and stocks in the Southern Ocean (30-80° E) determined by CHEMTAX analysis of HPLC pigment signatures (2010) Deep-Sea Res II, 57, pp. 758-778","Nielsen, L.T.; Marine Biological Section, University of Copenhagen, Strandpromenaden 5, Denmark",,,"Inter-Research",,,,,09483055,,MMFWE,,"English","Aquatic Microb. Ecol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-84863880573
